window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b><i>We thought death was the end, turns out it’s just the prologue.</i></b></p> <p><b>RUE</b></p> <p>I died, briefly. Then I came back. Now I’m determined to make the most of every minute I have left.</p> <p>Only problem is I’ve been saddled with supervision. Kane Deveraux is handsome, smug, and cold as a tombstone. So why does he make me feel something more powerful than death?</p> <p><b>KANE</b></p> <p>As a reaper, I have helped crossover thousands of souls. And not one of them have touched mine…until Rue Chamberlain. She’s stubborn, reckless, and maddeningly radiant.</p> <p>And for this centuries-old spirit, she’s a living woman that is absolutely off-limits. If I follow the rules, I will lose her. If I break them, I might lose everything.</p> <p><i>Grim</i> is a darkly romantic, wickedly funny tale of life, death, and a love that refuses to rest in peace.</p>"; 
